2026-04-24 | Count Buildings Receiving Sunlight

Question
Return number of buildings that can see sunlight.
	Approach
1.	Initialize:
		count = 0  
		maxHeight = 0  
2.	Traverse from left to right:
		for each building:
			if height > maxHeight:
				count++  
				update maxHeight  
3.	Return count  
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)


	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int countBuildings(vector<int>& arr) {
        int count = 0;
        int maxHeight = 0;
        for(int h : arr){
            if(h > maxHeight){
                count++;
                maxHeight = h;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
};
	Key Insight
A building sees sunlight only if it is **strictly taller than all buildings before it**.  
So we track a running maximum and count how many times it increases.
